	)
	(text "R2 = 280 Ohm"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 165.354 77.47 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "3fe07e57-b584-4bab-bae6-7ab5c960168d")
	)
	(text "in \"9.2 Typical Application\" of the document,\nthe capacitor shows 0.1 microfarad on the \ninput and 2.2 microfarad on the output.\n0.01 microfarad on the bypass capacitor \n(bypass pin)"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 158.242 114.046 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 0.635 0.635)
			)
		)
		(uuid "461bf8d4-b7e9-45ca-a489-5c0c2b9cf90c")
	)
	(text "just like how we did for the LEDs, also \ngo to DigiKey for the resistors. search \nup \"resistors 0805\", select\n\"chip resistors surface mount,\" and filter by\n- Resistance: 280 Ohms & 650 Ohms (couldn't find 650 so settled for 649)\n- Supplier Device Package: 0805 "
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 162.814 84.836 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 0.635 0.635)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "559632bd-eb4f-4d9e-8d8f-73ca85817389")
	)
	(text "since we couldn't\nfind any 650 Ohm\nresistors, we change\nR1 to 649 (the closest\none we found)"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 124.206 95.758 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 0.508 0.508)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "77c6c2d5-023c-49a1-af9a-9dbc37aadce7")
	)
	(text "go to the tps793 data sheet to be able to \nfind the capacitor / regulator information\nto understand what level capacitor u should\nbe using"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 143.764 78.994 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 0.635 0.635)
			)
		)
		(uuid "7c68c15d-66b2-4b25-afac-baf383b4fa5a")
	)
	(text "for the LEDs, go to DigiKey, filter by\ncolor: red & green\nsupplier device package: 2012 or 0805 \nproduct status: active\n\nyou end up with APTD2012LSURCK (red)\nand APTD2012LCGCK (green) "
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 120.142 115.824 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 0.635 0.635)
			)
		)
		(uuid "8bb60df4-4aed-4b29-8946-8baa8a08a841")
	)
	(text "essentially: \ninput 5V into resistor R1\nthe D1 (red) LED will voltage drop 1.75V\n(because we're using APTD2012LSURCK).\n5V - 1.75V = 3.25V drop across Resistor 1.\nthus, we use Ohm's Law to calculate this\nresistor, which is the voltage divided \nby current. \nR = V / I, so R1 voltage drop is \nR1 = 3.25V / 5mA = 650 Ohms"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 119.126 126.492 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 0.635 0.635)
			)
		)
		(uuid "920dae48-ff99-4ca8-b0a4-3109762c546c")
	)
	(text "R1 = 650 Ohm"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 110.236 78.74 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "ca3614ab-62f9-40f8-b28f-f7fda3bcea20")
	)
	(text "just like the red LED, we calculate this part too.\nwe're using APTD2012LCGCK for the green LED, so: \n- output that hits the resistor: 3.3V\n- the LED voltage drop of the green LED is 1.9V \nVoltage drop (across R2): 3.3V - 1.9V = 1.4V\n\naccording ot Ohm's Law, or R = V / I \nR3 = 1.4V / 5mA = 280 Ohms for this resistor"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 158.496 124.968 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 0.635 0.635)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "ca6a9097-8820-4d21-832d-2cccfc53e60a")
	)
	(text "the input voltage is 5V, and \nbecause we found the LEDs on DigiKey, \nwe found that the voltage drop was 1.75V.\n(it's in the \"Voltage - Forward (Vf) (Typ)\"\ncolumn)"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 116.586 84.836 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 0.635 0.635)
			)
		)
		(uuid "e347c7eb-5310-4d88-a774-8803b63cb04c")
	)
